as we can see from figure above, there are outliers on CNT_CHILDREN, AMT_INCOME_TOTAL and CNT_FAM_MEMBERS, we need to remove it because it can affect our model¶
In [6]:
def list_outliers(df, ft):
    q1 = df[ft].quantile(0.25)
    q3 = df[ft].quantile(0.75)
    IQR = q3-q1
    upper = q3 + 1.5 * IQR
    lower = q1 - 1.5 * IQR
    
    outlier = df.index[ (df[ft] < lower) | (df[ft] > upper)]
    return outlier

outlier_index = []

for feature in ['CNT_CHILDREN', 'AMT_INCOME_TOTAL', 'CNT_FAM_MEMBERS']:
    outlier_index.extend(list_outliers(df, feature))
    
def remove(df, routlier):
    routlier = sorted(set(routlier))
    df = df.drop(routlier)
    return df

df = remove(df,outlier_index)
